<p>The tone should always be respectful, gentle, and sincere. Avoid overly formal language or platitudes that might sound insincere.  Focusing on the positive memories of the mother and celebrating her life can offer a small measure of comfort.  Remember to tailor your message to your relationship with the bereaved and their cultural background, being mindful of any specific traditions or preferences.</p>
    

